,
  "bug_report_content": "Title: The CollectionUtils.removeAll method calls the ListUtils.retainAll method instead of the ListUtils.removeAll method.\nType: Bug | Priority: Major | Status: Closed | Resolution: Fixed\n\nDescription:\nThe CollectionUtils.removeAll method calls the ListUtils.retainAll method instead of the ListUtils.removeAll method.\n\nComments:\n\n[Stephen Colebourne]: Fixed in svn 348013, thanks\n\n[Maciej J\u00f3ziewicz]: Is there any hope for a 3.2.2 bugfix release?\n\n[Leif Hanack]: I question myself why there is no 3.2.2. bugfix release?\n\n[Thomas Neidhart]: There are plans to actually do this, but the priority is currently on releasing 4.0\n\n[Jochen Wiedmann]: The actual problem seems to me to be a gap in the test suite.",
  "fix_diff": "--- org.apache.commons.collections.CollectionUtils (buggy)\n+++ org.apache.commons.collections.CollectionUtils (fixed)\n@@ -1118,7 +1118,7 @@\n      * @since Commons Collections 3.3 (method existed in 3.2 but was completely broken)\n      */\n     public static Collection removeAll(Collection collection, Collection remove) {\n-        return ListUtils.retainAll(collection, remove);\n+        return ListUtils.removeAll(collection, remove);\n     }\n \n     //-----------------------------------------------------------------------"
}